n politics, sheds new light on the factors that led to the Iranian Revolution—the twentieth century's first major departure from Western political ideals—and helps explain the complexities surrounding the reception of Western ideologies in the Middle East.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aIntellectualsxPolitical activityzIran. 0aPolitical culturezIran. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/72804240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780292799561423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780292799561/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK